==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[excernere]]'', from ''[[ex-]]'', "out", and ''[[cernere]]'', "to separate".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːt|-iːt]]

===Verb===
'''to excrete''' ([[excretes]], [[excreted]], [[excreting]])

# ''(of an organism)'' to [[discharge]] from the [[system]].

